Subramanian K - Sample Use Case Walk through

This notebook is used to walk through "Fraud Claims Detection" use case with a sample open dataset.
Based on the nature of the dataset attributes, several Machine Learning techniques can be applied.
A glimpse of different options are shown below.


Each of the above family of ML approaches can be implemented using various algorithms.

In this walk through Supervised learning approach is considered. Primary factor that influenced this approach is nature of the dataset.
The dataset considered contains labelled observations i.e already identified fraud/No-fraud claims records from the past.

        binominal_variables.append(column)
    else:
        nominal_variables.append(column)

In Statictical terms ,Skewness indicates where the data is concentrated towards

  • Mean > Median
    • Positive Skew - Outliers are to the right side of the frequency distribution
  • Mean = Median
    • Zero Skew
  • Mean < Median
    • Negative Skew - Outliers are to the left of the frequency distribution

In real world applications of ML, Skewness needs to be handled. To keep it simple only inference is carried out for the dataset

Label Encoding and Dummy Variables

This is necessary for any ML Model since Mathematical algorithms can work only with numbers.

In [44]:
le = LabelEncoder()
for variable in binominal_variables:
    le.fit(dataSet[variable])
    dataSet[variable] = le.transform(dataSet[variable])
    print(le.classes_)

Lets fix the sampling issue and rebuild the model to show the effect of low miniroty samples

In [57]:

In [59]:

Lets Build an Ensemble Model

Only Boosting strategy is shown here, In actual applications research has to be done with Boosting, Bagging and Pasting or combination of those has to be tried

In [66]:

Conclusion:

1. Based on the dataset, an ML Family has to be choosed 
2. Perform Model Building using different algorithms for better performance 
3. For improved performance Ensemble apporaches can be employed 
4. For Big Data kind of distributed environment, Prefer Spark based learning 
5. Always perform initial data analysis, so Business insights from data can be verified with the stakeholders before spending time and money on Model Building
